articles.title: Leak Hints at First Intel Nvidia Chip After $5 Billion Partnership
articles.mainIdea: Leak Hints at First Intel Nvidia Chip After $5 Billion Partnership
articles.summary: GuruFocus.com: Leak Hints at First Intel Nvidia Chip After $5 Billion Partnership. Intel (INTC, Financials) and Nvidia (NVDA, Financials) may be preparing to ship their first jointly developed chip, according to leaked details about a laptop processor called Serpent Lake. The leak, shared by YouTube channel RedGamingTec, suggests the chip will combine Intel CPUs with Nvidia RTX graphics in a single design. Serpent Lake is expected to pair Intel's upcoming Titan Lake CPU architecture with Nvidia's RTX Rubin graphics, manufactured on TSMC's 3-nanometer process. Related tickers mentioned: AMD, NVDA, TSM.
